A.1 King County Lookup Lists Introduction A set of named lists that allow King Countyâ€™s various codifications to be converted into clearer text. For example, the following abbreviations are used to indicate the tax status of a parcel: ABBREVIATION CATEGORY T Taxable X Exempt O Operating The named list objects created in this section are used to de-code the various codification schemes used in the King County data. A.1.1 King County Jurisdictions Description Jurisdiction planning to annex this area. Link: Source Processing Steps Create string: The contents of the JURISDICTION table copy-and-pasted in the R environment. Create juris: A named vector of the jurisdictions and their abbreviations. juris <- str_split(string, pattern = "\n") %>% map(~ t(as.data.frame(str_split(.x,pattern = "\t")))) %>% as.data.frame() %>% set_names(c("CODE","NAME")) %>% set_rownames(NULL) %>% mutate_all(as.character) %>% pmap(~ set_names(..2, ..1)) str(juris) Upload to Drive folder <- as_id("0B5Pp4V6eCkhrZ3NHOEE0Sl9FbWc") tmp <- tempfile() write_rds(juris,tmp) drive_upload(tmp, folder,name = "kc-jurisdictions.rds") A.1.2 King County Present Use Categories Description Description text here Links: Source Data Metadata Processing Steps Create pu_ready: A lookup list of present use categories and their 2-character codes pu_fp <- root_file("./1-data/2-external/EXTR_LookUp.csv") maybe_make(pu_fp,{ dr_id <- "0B5Pp4V6eCkhrN212NEFOeVV6T2s" d <- drive_get(id = dr_id) tmp <- tempfile() d %>% drive_download(path = tmp) unzip_dir <- root_file("./1-data/2-external") unzip(zipfile = tmp,exdir = unzip_dir) }) pu_ready <- read_csv(pu_fp) %>% rename_all(to_screaming_snake_case) %>% filter(LU_TYPE %in% 102) %>% select(LU_DESCRIPTION, LU_ITEM) %>% pmap(~purrr::set_names(..1,..2)) Load juris: A named vector of the jurisdictions and their abbreviations. juris_fp <- root_file("./1-data/3-interim/kc-jurisdictions.rds") maybe_make(juris_fp, { dr_id <- as_id("0B5Pp4V6eCkhrTU9Kd3hVVVkyZjQ") d <- drive_get(dr_id) d %>% drive_download(path = juris_fp) }) juris <- read_rds(juris_fp)
